
The purpose of user stories is to capture the essence of what a user wants to achieve with the software in a concise and understandable manner. They help software engineers to prioritize and plan their work based on the needs of the user or customer.

Here are some examples of user stories:

As a student, I want presonalized data for my research paper, so that I can put valuable information in my paper.

As a social media user, I want to be able to post images with my status updates, about the places I travel around the world.

As an online shopper for travel, I want to be able to filter search results for places to travel, so that I can quickly find places within my desires.

As a traveler, I want to be able to see places in the world, so that I can make informed decisions about where to go.

As a curious person, I want to be able to access intersting websites and read data easily and filter it the way I want.
